---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AppDemo from '../components/AppDemo.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="About — The earned-media engine for Higher Education"
  description="701am was built by a team that spent 20 years in education visibility. Now we're automating it for the AI era — earned media that compounds instead of resets."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <header class="about-hero">
    <div class="hero-atmos"><div class="grid"></div><div class="glow g1"></div><div class="glow g2"></div><div class="glow g3"></div></div>
    <div class="wrap" style="position:relative;z-index:1">
      <div class="eyebrow">About 701am</div>
      <h1>The old playbook isnt converting. <em class="grad">We wrote the new one.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">AI chatbots, TikTok, and new discovery channels have rewritten how prospective students find schools — just as the enrollment cliff arrives. The old playbook isn't built for this world. 701am is.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- STORY -->
  <article class="about-prose">
    <div class="seg">Where we started</div>
    <p class="big">We've spent two decades on one question: when someone is choosing a school, how do they decide — and how do you make sure your program is in that decision?</p>
    <p>For most of that time, the answer was search. We built and operated a network of education properties — <strong>CollegeChoice</strong>, <strong>TheBestSchools</strong>, <strong>CollegeConsensus</strong>, <strong>BestCollegeReviews</strong>, <strong>ValueColleges</strong>, and hundreds more — that millions of prospective students used to compare programs. We understood exactly how applicants research, what makes a program credible to them, and how to put the right institutions in front of the right students at the moment they were deciding.</p>
    <p>That's not adjacent experience. That <em>is</em> the job 701am does. We just spent twenty years doing it manually, site by site, before the technology existed to automate it.</p>

    <div class="seg">Then the ground moved</div>
    <p>A few years ago, the behavior we'd built a career around started to change. Applicants stopped beginning with a Google search and a comparison site. They started asking an AI assistant — <em>"what's the best online MSW for working adults?"</em> — and taking the short, confident answer it gave them. They discovered programs through TikTok videos. They made decisions in channels that didn't exist a decade ago.</p>
    <p class="pull">The shortlist was forming somewhere we couldn't see, in places we couldn't optimize for with the old playbook.</p>
    <p>We watched institutions that had spent years and fortunes on their visibility quietly disappear from the answer. Not because their programs got worse — because the place the decision happened moved, and the old ways couldn't follow it there.</p>

    <div class="seg">Why 701am exists</div>
    <p>The signals that make a program credible haven't actually changed. Rankings. Real outcomes data. Coverage in publications people trust. Those still decide who gets shortlisted — it's just that <strong>an AI reads them now too</strong>, alongside the humans, alongside the TikTok algorithm. The work that earns those signals is the same work we've done for two decades. It's just slow, manual, and expensive — which is why most institutions only do it in bursts, around a campaign, and then let it reset.</p>
    <p>701am is the machine we wish we'd had: a swarm of agents that does that earned-media work continuously, across every channel that matters — so a school's visibility compounds instead of resetting, and so it shows up in the AI answer, the search result, the press, and the social feed, all at once.</p>
    <p class="pull">We're not a PR firm that discovered AI. We're education-visibility operators who spent two decades on this exact problem, building the tool the next twenty years need.</p>
  </article>

  <!-- CREDENTIALS -->
  <section class="creds">
    <div class="atmos"><div class="dg dg1"></div></div>
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ch">
          <div class="eb">The track record</div>
          <h2>Not a first attempt at education visibility.</h2>
          <p>We came from the trenches, and the numbers prove it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="creds-grid">
          <div class="cred"><div class="cv">20+</div><div class="cl">Years building and operating education-visibility properties</div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cv">Hundreds</div><div class="cl">Of education lead-gen properties built, operated, and optimized</div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cv">Millions</div><div class="cl">Of prospective student interactions across that network</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE'VE BUILT -->
  <section class="past">
    <div class="ph">
      <div class="eb">Built &amp; operated</div>
      <h2>A network applicants actually used.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="past-list">
      <span class="pl">CollegeChoice</span>
      <span class="pl">TheBestSchools</span>
      <span class="pl">CollegeConsensus</span>
      <span class="pl">BestCollegeReviews</span>
      <span class="pl">ValueColleges</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- VALUES -->
  <section class="values">
    <div class="value">
      <i class="ti ti-shield-check"></i>
      <div><h3>Earned, never faked</h3><p>No fabricated coverage, no invented quotes, no manufactured rankings. Earned media only works if it's actually earned — and in higher ed, anything less is a liability.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="value">
      <i class="ti ti-arrows-up-right"></i>
      <div><h3>Visibility should compound</h3><p>The old model resets every campaign. We build so every placement, ranking, and citation makes the next one easier — visibility as an asset, not a recurring expense.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="value">
      <i class="ti ti-focus-2"></i>
      <div><h3>One world, done deeply</h3><p>We don't serve every industry. We serve higher ed — because depth beats breadth, and because it's the world we've lived in for twenty years.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SEE THE PRODUCT -->
  <section class="band wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <div class="sec-eyebrow">See the platform</div>
      <h2>A swarm of agents doing the <em class="grad">work we used to do</em>.</h2>
      <p>701am automates what we spent two decades doing by hand — researching angles, earning coverage, and tying every placement to enrollment.</p>
    </div>
    <AppDemo />
  </section>

  <!-- CLOSING -->
  <section class="closing">
    <div class="catmos"><div class="cg"></div></div>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="pill-badge"><span class="tagm">Filed at sunrise</span></div>
      <h2>Let's get your program <em class="grad">found</em>.</h2>
      <p>The enrollment cliff is coming. The institutions that invest in visibility now will be the ones students find when it matters most.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"><i class="ti ti-sparkles"></i>Start a conversation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
